id: pm-vhx6
title: "list/search: trim default filters/projection/sorting/now trailer in compact/agent mode"
description: "agent-UX audit F3: list/search always emit a ~19-key filters trailer + projection/sorting/now even in compact mode (more metadata than data on small result sets). Emit only non-default/agent-supplied keys in compact mode and gate the trailer behind --full/--explain. Complements [[pm-rmjy]]."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:cli",token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-06-07T17:04:17.220Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-08T06:14:22.649Z"
assignee: codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-mpbb
comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T19:58:20.957Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Execution kickoff: duplicate-check run via pm search/list/context (2026-06-07T19:57Z). Selected for this focused PR with pm-6l17 + pm-jozc to improve agent token efficiency and never-block UX in one coherent CLI surface batch."
  "2026-06-07T20:17:56.835Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Implemented compact trailer trimming: when list/search run in explicit compact mode (including MCP narrow defaults), output now omits projection/sorting/now trailer metadata and emits only active/user-supplied filter keys (plus runtime filter summaries when present). Non-compact/full/fields flows remain unchanged for diagnostics. Updated unit/integration coverage for CLI and MCP compact output shape. Targeted verification passed (3 files, 134 tests)."
  "2026-06-07T20:47:40.556Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Docs/contracts sync completed: updated docs/COMMANDS.md + docs/AGENT_GUIDE.md for compact list/search metadata behavior and read-command --tags alias support; refreshed contract snapshot (pnpm contracts:update, contracts:check clean). pm-changelog generation check passed via direct command (CHANGELOG unchanged). npm view pm-changelog latest-version lookup could not complete in this environment (network stall), so latest-version verification is limited to successful in-repo generator behavior."
  "2026-06-07T21:31:55.903Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Full verification pass complete: coverage gate now passes at 100% statements/branches/functions/lines (2564 tests, 149 files). Local quality/security gates pass (pnpm quality:static, security:scan). Dependency/security checks: pnpm audit moderate returns zero advisories; pnpm outdated reports commander 14.0.3 -> 15.0.0 as the only outdated root dependency. Local telemetry/health checks: health --check-only --check-telemetry summary reports ok=true with warning_count=0; telemetry status and stats confirm command events captured for manual workflows. Manual temp-directory dogfood validated init/create/list/search/update/close/package-catalog, list/search --tags alias behavior, compact metadata trimming (no projection/sorting/now trailer), and MCP pm_list top-level filter ingestion against a temp PM_PATH."
  "2026-06-07T21:31:56.911Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"External observability note: sentry-cli project issue reads remain blocked by token scope (403 permission denied), so this run uses local telemetry + health evidence only, per agreed execution mode."
  "2026-06-07T21:35:50.937Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"Final pre-PR rerun after smoke-test relocation: node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage still 100% across statements/branches/functions/lines; contracts snapshot check, static quality gate, and secret scan all pass."
  "2026-06-08T06:14:22.649Z",codex-agent-ux-reliability-20260607,"PR review-loop follow-up (CodeRabbit actionable comments): replaced compact list/search unsafe casts with explicit compact/verbose result unions; compact payloads now remain token-light while preserving typed contracts. Added compile-safe now timestamp fallbacks in comments-audit/normalize for list consumers that require deterministic generated timestamps. Verification rerun: focused list/search suites pass (155 tests), full coverage remains 100% (2564 tests), and contracts/static/security gates remain green."
